9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 9, L.D. 45, “An Act Allowing the
10 Department of Corrections to Offset Some of the Costs of Technology Provided to
11 Residents of Correctional Facilities”
12 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 2. 34-A MRSA §1403, sub-§14 is enacted to read:
14 14. Technology fee. The commissioner may establish a reasonable fee, as provided
15 in this subsection, for the use of technology, including, but not limited to, computers, laptop
16 computers and external storage devices, that is provided to residents of correctional
17 facilities in connection with educational or vocational programs, remote work or other
18 purposes. For each calendar month in which the technology is used by a resident, as defined
19 in section 3015, subsection 1, paragraph B, the fee charged may not exceed 7% of the
20 money received by the resident, from any source, during the month after any deductions
21 for court-ordered or statutory obligations, including, but not limited to, child support, court
22 filing fees, victim restitution, fines, facility restitution, facility monetary sanctions, medical
23 and dental services fees and room and board, or $35, whichever is less. The commissioner
24 may not charge a fee under this subsection for:
25 A. Technology that is provided to a resident for the purpose of research related to a
26 criminal case or civil lawsuit in which the resident is involved; or
27 B. Technology that is provided to a resident who has received money totaling less than
28 $100, from any source, during the calendar month after any deductions that are
29 provided for in this subsection.
30 Money received by the resident and directly deposited into a telephone call account
31 established by the department under section 3039, subsection 4 for the sole purpose of
32 paying for use of the department's client telephone system is not subject to this subsection.
33 Money received by the resident as a credit improvement loan in accordance with section
34 3039, subsection 6 is not subject to this subsection.
35 A correctional facility shall collect any fees received under this subsection and deposit them
36 into the Resident Technology Fund established in section 1220.
