13 SUMMARY
1144 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, amends the bill by
1155 providing financial limits on the proposed technology fee that the Commissioner of
1166 Corrections may impose by requiring that the fee may not exceed 7% of the money received
1177 by a resident, from any source, for the calendar month in which the technology is used by
1188 a resident after accounting for the specified deductions or $35, whichever is less. It also
1199 prohibits charging a technology fee to a resident who receives less than $100, from any
2200 source, during the calendar month after any deductions are applied. The amendment
2211 clarifies that money received by the resident and directly deposited into a correctional
2222 facility telephone call account is not considered when calculating money received by a
2233 resident. Money received by a resident as part of a credit improvement loan is also not
2244 considered when calculating the money received by a resident. The amendment also adds
2255 an appropriations and allocations section.
